<span class=\"subj\" subj=\"polit\" q=\"esp\">politics</span>)</span> <span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">to choose somebody as a candidate in an election; to choose somebody as your representative</span><ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">She was adopted as parliamentary candidate for Wood Green.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">The people adopted him as their patron saint.</span></li></ul>      </li></span><div class=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"collapse\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"wordorigin\" id=\"adopt_unbox_3\"><span class=\"box_title\">Word Origin</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\">late 15th cent.: via French from Latin <span class=\"ei\">adoptare</span>, from <span class=\"ei\">ad-</span> ‘to’ + <span class=\"ei\">optare</span> ‘choose’.</span></span></span></div></ol><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/adopt\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">adopt</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/academic/adopt\" title=\" definition in Academic English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">adopt</span></a> in the Oxford Learner's Dictionary of Academic English</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/adopt\">adopt</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["adolescent adjective","Adonis noun","adopt verb","adopted adjective","adoptee noun"]}]]